{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17649954","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17649954"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T21:08:23+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T21:08:23+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18383"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18383","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18383"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11101"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74430"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11101","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11101"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18383"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59921"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"12"},{"type":"tags","id":"14"},{"type":"tags","id":"34"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"260"},{"type":"tags","id":"1061"},{"type":"tags","id":"2843"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"5810"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25740"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25742"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74430","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/74430"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 58-year-old man presents to the hospital with severe pain and swelling in his left knee. He underwent knee surgery two weeks ago. He reports a fever and an inability to move the joint. On examination, he appears unwell with a temperature of 38.5\u00b0C. The left knee is swollen, warm, and tender with limited range of motion. Aspiration of the joint reveals purulent synovial fluid. Imaging shows significant inflammation and damage to the articular cartilage.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Reactive arthritis","Rheumatoid arthritis","Gout","Acute septic arthritis","Pseudogout"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with symptoms consistent with \u003Cstrong\u003Eacute septic arthritis\u003C/strong\u003E, including joint pain, swelling, fever, and purulent synovial fluid. The recent knee surgery increases the risk of bacterial infection in the joint, leading to septic arthritis. The presence of pus in the synovial fluid and the rapid onset of symptoms are key indicators of this condition.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EReactive arthritis\u003C/strong\u003E is typically associated with a preceding infection elsewhere in the body, such as a gastrointestinal or genitourinary infection, and does not usually present with purulent synovial fluid.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERheumatoid arthritis\u003C/strong\u003E is a chronic inflammatory condition that affects multiple joints and is not typically associated with purulent synovial fluid or acute fever.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGout\u003C/strong\u003E is characterised by the deposition of urate crystals in the joint, leading to acute inflammation, but it does not typically present with purulent synovial fluid or fever.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPseudogout\u003C/strong\u003E involves the deposition of calcium pyrophosphate crystals in the joint, causing inflammation, but like gout, it does not usually present with purulent synovial fluid or fever.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Acute septic arthritis is characterised by joint pain, swelling, fever, and purulent synovial fluid.","Septic arthritis can lead to irreversible joint damage if not treated promptly.","Recent joint surgery increases the risk of septic arthritis due to potential introduction of bacteria."],"references":["Patton, K. T., \u0026 Thibodeau, G. A. (2018). Anthony\u0027s Textbook of Anatomy \u0026 Physiology-E-Book: Anthony\u0027s Textbook of Anatomy \u0026 Physiology-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Sud, A., \u0026 Ranjan, R. (2021). Textbook of Orthopaedics, 2e-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Dandy, D. J., \u0026 Edwards, D. J. (2009). Essential Orthopaedics and Trauma E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","MacGregor R, Byerly DW. Anatomy, Bony Pelvis and Lower Limb: Foot Bones. 2023 May 23. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 32491379","Ombregt, L. (2013). A System of Orthopaedic Medicine-E-Book: A System of Orthopaedic Medicine-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59921"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18383"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59921","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/59921"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-25T05:19:02+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-25T05:20:39+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11101"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74430"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"12","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/12"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc4b","name":"Rheumatology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:47+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"14","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/14"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udda0","name":"Infectious Diseases","synonyms":[